Not at all. The monster just let out a roar and tried to charge directly at Sasarin. Thank goodness, although Sasarin was large in size, he was still quite agile and managed to dodge in time. However, Nisi couldn't help but scream, nearly slipping off Sasarin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nisi shouted.
"Target their heads!"
"This is too hard!"
Sasalin let out a roar, circled around, and flew toward the mountain he called home. The black monster followed closely, but when it was attacked by fire from behind, it became visibly startled. The monster still hadn't realized it now had another opponent. Sasalin slowed down and then swung his tail fiercely at the monster's head, knocking it off course, making the monster even more panicked.
The monster roared, its throat emitting a hissing sound, flying straight upward while continuously spewing something into the air. Suddenly, the surroundings turned pitch black, as if the monster were siphoning the light from the sky and replacing it with eternal darkness.
Sassarin blacked out for a moment, trying to step back, but found himself colliding with the branches and falling onto the empty ground. The monster seemed to clearly know where Sassarin had fallen, flying straight toward him and dragging the dark cloud with it.
"Kaiyer!" Tenuk shouted, bursting out of the clouds and beginning to circle, trying to locate Nisi and Sasilin below in the darkness. "What should we do? Kaiyer...? Kaiyer, where are you?"
Nisi struggled to her feet. She felt certain she had broken a bone, but her strange, unnatural ability to heal was already beginning to take effect. Sasarin's situation was different; he lay helplessly on the ground, leaning against a tree he had knocked over. Nisi made her way painfully toward Sasarin, but her vision was pitch black, and she could hardly see anything. Horrible shadows surrounded her, and something was shrieking within them.
A terrifying club-like tail smashed down onto the ground, knocking Nici to the ground. She noticed the tail flailing around wildly, but it seemed its target wasn't her. Nici barely caught a glimpse as the monster roared and clawed at the shadow it had created. Something moved instantaneously in the darkness, waiting for the right moment to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot cracked through the air, and the monster immediately fell silent, collapsing to the ground motionless. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth of the situation. Kael stood on top of the monster's corpse, holding his rifle, breathing heavily.
“That was... this was one of the strangest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tanto Cartel..." Cayler panted. Somehow, his eyes were glowing with black light, and a surge of dark energy was flowing through his body. But just as Cayler began to speak, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes reverted back to their normal yellow.
After a while, Nisi finally realized what had happened. They all knew that Cayler possessed an eerie shadow ability, but he rarely used it because most people considered this ability extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nisi didn't know that Cayler could use this ability in any darkness. Moreover, from Cayler's reaction, it seemed that even he was surprised himself.
"Are you okay?" Nishi couldn't help but ask.
"I'm fine. I've killed that thing, and I'll be okay soon," Cayl looked at his "masterpiece," and at that moment, Tenuk fell beside him, reverting back to his original Spast form.
Now, the monster is motionless, allowing them to take a good look at what it really is. Its skin is dark and glossy, covered with a layer of sticky liquid that adheres firmly to its body. It has four wings and four legs, each ending in long, sharp claws. On its skull, there are two straight horns.
Tunuk and Kayel hadn't even had time to ask what the hell this thing was when a monster screamed and burst out of the nearby bushes. At that moment, a familiar car crashed into the monster's side, sending it sliding several meters before coming to a stop by Nisi's feet. Nisi didn't hesitate; he grabbed a shot gun and fired a shot at the monster's head, killing it instantly.
"Ugh..." Retwick muttered as he sat in the driver's seat, then awkwardly turned off the engine and climbed down from the truck. "Er, I didn't mean to. Are you all okay?"
"you missed all the good parts!" Tenuk snorted. "Where did you go?"
"it was you who left me behind. I've tried my best to catch up..." Retweik sighed. "Excuse me, what are these terrible things?"
Rettwik's question was answered by Sasilin, who had already stood up. He was covered in wounds and scratches, looked a bit dazed, but his injuries seemed not to be serious.
"You have slain the corrupted ones! Those infected creatures. When the corruption attacked your god, these beings were left behind here."
"Are you saying... that we... helped kill the terrible monster god?" Tenuk stammered a bit.
"Yes, that's true. There might be more corrupters. But I can't just shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And fighting two to one isn't fair, is it?" Sazalin stepped up to Cayler and patted his head. "Thank you, little guy. You reminded me of my old friend Alcardin. Only you aren't as ruthless as him, and you don't have his destructive power over the universe."
"Uh... thank you... I think..." Cayler shrugged. "So, uh, did we complete the mission?"
Nisi shrugged, picked up her camera, and took a few pictures of the monsters that were clearly already dead. Then she drew out her favorite dagger—the exquisite Death's Dagger—and began cutting off one of the monsters' horns, then another. However, the moment Nisi finished the cutting, the monsters suddenly burst into flames and quickly turned into piles of ash. Even the horns she had cut off turned to ash as well.
"Alright... this really has its pros and cons..." Nisi sighed. "At least I still have the photos, right?"
